Talking Points:
1) Decide roles on the Board
2) Resolve Binnur's issue/request
3) Determine what to do with Allan's various complaints
4) Get moving on preventive maintenance
...Resolve the planters 1, 4, 7, 9 - I think I heard Cam say that the new trees are going to be simply placed in the planters in their existing containers vs. filling the planters with dirt - If I heard this right, I don't understand how these trees will thrive - they will become root bound very quickly perhaps an alternate solution is to build a wood planter that drops into the existing space but prevents the dirt from being in contact with the stucco and allows water drainage at the bottom and through the existing drain openings vs seeping into the walls
...Do something about the gardener as the front planters, especially, aren't getting proper attention
...Repair the landscape lighting, last I checked, most of it is not working
...Determine if we want the motion sensor lights/alarms in the alleys to function, last time I walked through I don't think any of the alarms were working
...Plan painting of the interior courtyard - this is far overdue
...Understand what is going on with the roof - I didn't bring it up in the meeting, but like Binnur, I have found entire tiles and pieces of roof tiles on my deck
...Determine if we care that the courtyard drains into the garage at various areas - I actually think this might be by design vs. a flaw
...Decide if we want to hire someone to regularly maintain/clean the garage - specifically the loose trash and recycling that builds up

description:
Talking Points:
1) Decide roles on the Board
2) Resolve Binnur's issue/request
3) Determine what to do with Allan's various complaints
4) Get moving on preventive maintenance
...Resolve the planters 1, 4, 7, 9 - I think I heard Cam say that the new trees are going to be simply placed in the planters in their existing containers vs. filling the planters with dirt - If I heard this right, I don't understand how these trees will thrive - they will become root bound very quickly perhaps an alternate solution is to build a wood planter that drops into the existing space but prevents the dirt from being in contact with the stucco and allows water drainage at the bottom and through the existing drain openings vs seeping into the walls
...Do something about the gardener as the front planters, especially, aren't getting proper attention
...Repair the landscape lighting, last I checked, most of it is not working
...Determine if we want the motion sensor lights/alarms in the alleys to function, last time I walked through I don't think any of the alarms were working
...Plan painting of the interior courtyard - this is far overdue
...Understand what is going on with the roof - I didn't bring it up in the meeting, but like Binnur, I have found entire tiles and pieces of roof tiles on my deck
...Determine if we care that the courtyard drains into the garage at various areas - I actually think this might be by design vs. a flaw
...Decide if we want to hire someone to regularly maintain/clean the garage - specifically the loose trash and recycling that builds up
